changeVaultFactoryOwner(address).details: this function is used to tranfer ownership and all roles from one account to another while also removing all permissions on the previous account

constructor.details: _disableInitializers prevents future reinitializations [_disableInitializers](https://docs.openzeppelin.com/contracts/5.x/api/proxy#Initializable-_disableInitializers--) for more info

createVault(address,address,string,bool).details: this function is used to create a vault and takes a native token payment of a specified amount which can be viewed using the creationFee function

params.projectOwner: the address of the owner and admin of the vault baing created
params.rewardToken: the address of the erc20 token to reward users with
params.useTokenForPayment: use token for payment instead of eth

returns._0: vault the address of the created vault

creationFee().details: this function is used to check the current vault creation fee in eth

returns.erc20Fee: the creation fee value in ERC20 Token
returns.ethFee: the creation fee value in ETH/Native Token

erc20PaymentToken().details: this function allows one to view the current erc20 payment token used in vault creation which is also an option aside from using the ETH/Native Token

feeReceiver().details: this function is used to check the fee receiver the factory is currently using

returns._0: feeReceiver the address where the vault creation payments will be sent to

getImplementationDetails().details: this function is used to check the current vault implementation details

returns._1: contractType the contract type of the implementation
returns._2: version the version of the implementation
returns.implementationAddress: the vault implementation the factory is currently using

getRoleAdmin(bytes32).details: Returns the admin role that controls `role`. See {grantRole} and {revokeRole}. To change a role's admin, use {_setRoleAdmin}.

getVaultInfo(address).details: this fuction is used to check the vault's info stored in the registry

returns._0: vaultInfo the vault information stored in te factory

grantPermit(address).details: this function is used to grant controller permissions on controller only restricted functions

grantRole(bytes32,address).details: Grants `role` to `account`. If `account` had not been already granted `role`, emits a {RoleGranted} event. Requirements: - the caller must have ``role``'s admin role. May emit a {RoleGranted} event.

initialize(address,address,address,uint2.details: this is used in palce of a constructor to initialize a proxy's state using this implemetation's logic

params._creationFee: the amount of native tokens the non owner/controller needs to pay to create a new vault
params._erc20PaymentToken: the address of the erc20 token the non owner/controller needs to pay to create a new vault
params._feeReceiver: the address where the fees from vault creation is going to be sent
params.erc20CreationFee: the amount of erc20 tokens the non owner/controller needs to pay to create a new vault
params.initialAdmin: the initial admin and the owner of the contract
params.vaultImplementation: the vault implementation address to be used in creating new vaults

isController(address).details: this fucntion is used to check if a given address is a controller or not

owner().details: this function is used to check who the current owner of the factory is

proxiableUUID().details: Implementation of the ERC1822 {proxiableUUID} function. This returns the storage slot used by the implementation. It is used to validate the implementation's compatibility when performing an upgrade. IMPORTANT: A proxy pointing at a proxiable contract should not be considered proxiable itself, because this risks bricking a proxy that upgrades to it, by delegating to itself until out of gas. Thus it is critical that this function revert if invoked through a proxy. This is guaranteed by the `notDelegated` modifier.

renounceRole(bytes32,address).details: Revokes `role` from the calling account. Roles are often managed via {grantRole} and {revokeRole}: this function's purpose is to provide a mechanism for accounts to lose their privileges if they are compromised (such as when a trusted device is misplaced). If the calling account had been revoked `role`, emits a {RoleRevoked} event. Requirements: - the caller must be `callerConfirmation`. May emit a {RoleRevoked} event.

revokePermit(address).details: this function is used to revoke the controller permission of an address

revokeRole(bytes32,address).details: Revokes `role` from `account`. If `account` had been granted `role`, emits a {RoleRevoked} event. Requirements: - the caller must have ``role``'s admin role. May emit a {RoleRevoked} event.

setERC20PaymentToken(address).details: this function is used to update the erc20 payment token used to pay for the vault creation

setFeeReceiver(address).details: this function is used to update the fee receiver on the factory

totalVaults().details: this function is used to check the total amount of vaults created by the factory

returns._0: totalVaults the amount of vaults currently created by the factory

updateCreationFee(uint256,uint256).details: this function is used to update the vault creation fee the users needed to pay to create a new vault

params.newCreationFee: the new creation fee that users need to pay to create a vault in ETH
params.newERC20CreationFee: the new creation fee for ERC20 token payment that users need to pay to create a vault in ETH

updateImplementation(address).details: this function is used to update the vault implementation used in creating new vaults

params.newImplementation: the address of the new vault implementation

updateVaultInfo(address).details: this function is used to sync the info from the vault to the factory for any vault deployed by this factory and can only be accessed by the owner of the vault and the factory owner/controller

params.vault: the vault address that is in the factory's registry

upgradeToAndCall(address,bytes).details: Upgrade the implementation of the proxy to `newImplementation`, and subsequently execute the function call encoded in `data`. Calls {_authorizeUpgrade}. Emits an {Upgraded} event.

typeDescriptions.typeString: function () view external returns (struct VaultInfo memory)
